What does this validation function check?

```javascript
function validateAge() {
  let age = document.getElementById('age-input').value;
  let error = document.getElementById('age-error');

  if (age === '') {
    error.textContent = 'Age is required.';
    return false;
  }

  if (age < 13) {
    error.textContent = 'You must be at least 13 to sign up.';
    return false;
  }

  if (age > 120) {
    error.textContent = 'Please enter a valid age.';
    return false;
  }

  error.textContent = '';
  return true;
}
```

What does this code do?

```javascript
fetch('https://api.weather.com/current?city=Denver')
  .then(response => response.json())
  .then(data => {
    document.getElementById('temp').textContent = data.temperature + '°F';
    document.getElementById('conditions').textContent = data.description;
  });
```

Users report that the discount code 'SAVE20' is not working. Look at this code — what is the bug?

```javascript
function applyDiscount() {
  let code = document.getElementById('discount-code').value;

  if (code === 'save20') {
    let price = document.getElementById('total').textContent;
    let discounted = price * 0.80;
    document.getElementById('total').textContent = '$' + discounted;
  } else {
    document.getElementById('discount-error').textContent = 'Invalid code.';
  }
}
```
